The order of 8 parameters of the USER's function GRADIENT of CONDUCTIVITY
in the direction number NDIR (1 to 3) of coordinate axis
at time TEMPS, at point X,Y,Z, 
for the PLSVO of type number NO_TYPE_OBJECT
(1:POINT, 2:LINE, 3:SURFACE, 4:VOLUME, 5:OBJECT )
the directory number NO_OBJECT
for a temperature TEMPER, known or unknown, (case not linear),
must be

DERIVEE_CONDUCTIVITY( TEMPS, X, Y, Z, NO_TYPE_OBJET, NO_OBJET, NDIR, TEMPER ) 

and be programmed with respect to LU grammar
(cf documentation and examples of the debut menu)

All these parameters will be initialized during its call.
These parameters can be used or not, but have to be present
in the definition of GRADIENT of CONDUCTIVITY in the direction NDIR.
 
EXAMPLE:
deffunc dconductivity( t, x, y, z, no_type_objet, materiau, ndir, temper ) ;
if    ndir=1
then dconductivity=2;
else if ndir=2
      then dconductivity=4;
      else dconductivity=0;
      finif;  
finif;
endfunc; 

Remark: the LU function nuobjt( p1, p2 ) gives the
number of the PLSVO of type p1 with the name p2.
